ENTRY            F1539   20260115   20260305   20260305       F106
SUBENT        F1539001   20260115   20260305   20260305       F106
BIB                 13         34
TITLE      Determination of neutron yield from 'THICK' Be target
           irradiated with 21.5 MeV protons using a proton beam
           monitoring system
AUTHOR     (Yu.E.Titarenko,A.A.Arkhipov,S.A.Balyuk,V.F.Batyaev,
           M.V.Batyaeva,V.D.Davidenko,V.M.Zhivun,Ya.O.Zaritskiy,
           A.A.Kovalishin,M.V.Kotelniy,A.S.Kirsanov,T.V.Kulevoy,
           I.V.Mednikov,B.A.Novikov,A.V.Orlov,K.V.Pavlov,
           V.S.Stolbunov,A.Yu.Titarenko,R.S.Tikhonov,
           M.N.Shlenskii,N.A.Kovalenko)
INSTITUTE  (4RUSITE)
REFERENCE  (J,PAN,88,464,2025)
           #doi:10.1134/S1063778825600642
FACILITY   (LINAC,4RUSITE) NS-21M facility, based on the I-2
           linear proton accelerator
METHOD     (ACTIV,GSPEC)
DETECTOR   (HPGE) Measurements were conducted using two gamma-
           ray spectrometers equipped with coaxial GC2518-type
           detectors, each having an energy resolution of 1.8 keV
           at the 1332 keV gamma line of 60Co.
MONITOR    (29-CU-0(P,X)30-ZN-62,,SIG)
           (29-CU-0(P,X)30-ZN-63,,SIG)
SAMPLE     13 natCu samples (15 mu-m thick) were irradiated.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) Cross section error includes the
           uncertainty of the monitor reactions, the uncertainty
           of the count rate in a peak, the uncertainty of
           absolute detection efficiency, the uncertainty of
           quantum yield, the uncertainty of gamma quanta
           self-absorption in a sample.
ADD-RES    Neutron yield of the NS-21M facility, based on the
           I-2 linear proton accelerator and 3.8 mm thick Be
           target under bombardment by 21.5 MeV protons was
           obtained: (1.35+-0.09)*10**(-2).
STATUS     (TABLE,,Yu.E.Titarenko+,J,PAN,88,464,2025) Table 4
HISTORY    (20260115C)
